Been going here for a long time, and am completely enamored with the food, service, prices and family-run atmosphere every time.
I take everyone that visits there for a taste of 'real mexican food' and it's one of the only places I love enough to review.
The prices are great, and the food is both incredibly tasty and remarkably consistent from visit-to-visit.
I honestly don't know why, but it's also the only Mexcan restaurant where I always leave feeling full in a good way - I've never felt the typical pains associated with overeating after leaving, even when I've certainly gotten too full.
I recommend the Enchiladas, beef tacos and tamale in their #12, or the steak gorditas in #13.
They're slammed during lunch on weekdays so get there by 11AM or after 1PM.

Really good food at the given price.
